        "title": "Fragment not being displayed when called from Activity",
        "body": "<p>I have an Activity which prompts the user with a dialog (which is a Fragment) when a button is pressed. When the user presses OK on this dialog/fragment, it takes the user to the Camera app to take a picture. This picture should be stored and passed onto a new Fragment. The new Fragment should be just the picture, and cover the entire screen.<\/p>\n\n<p>onActivityResult() is called in the Activity to handle actions from the dialog. Here, I try to bring up the Fragment that consists of just the picture. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>AddChainItemFragment addChainItemFragment = new AddChainItemFragment();\nBundle bundle = new Bundle();\n// imageUri is the URI of the camera image that was just taken\nBitmap chainItem = MediaStore.Images.Media.getBitmap(getContentResolver(), imageUri);\nbundle.putParcelable(\"ChainItem\", chainItem); // add image to bundle\naddChainItemFragment.setArguments(bundle); // pass bundle to fragment\nFragmentTransaction ft = getSupportFragmentManager().beginTransaction();\nft.replace(R.id.llHomeActivity, addChainItemFragment); // replace activity's layout (linearlayout) with the new fragment\nft.commit();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When I run the debugger I can see that the AddChainItemFragment's onCreateView() method is definitely called. The Fragment is simply an ImageView and I set that image to be what was passed into the bundle from the activity. I also included <code>view.bringToFront()<\/code> in onCreateView(). The onCreateView code for this Fragment is here: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> @Override\npublic View onCreateView(LayoutInflater inflater, ViewGroup container,\n                         Bundle savedInstanceState) {\n    Bitmap chainItem = getArguments().getParcelable(\"ChainItem\");\n    View view = inflater.inflate(R.layout.fragment_add_chain_item, container, false);\n    ivChainItem = (ImageView) view.findViewById(R.id.ivChainItem);\n    ivChainItem.setImageBitmap(chainItem);\n    view.bringToFront();\n    return view;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The Fragment's layout: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;ImageView xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n    xmlns:tools=\"http://schemas.android.com/tools\"\n    android:id=\"@+id/ivChainItem\"\n    android:layout_width=\"match_parent\"\n    android:layout_height=\"match_parent\"\n    tools:context=\"myapp.heisenberg.chainmaker.AddChainItemFragment\"&gt;\n&lt;/ImageView&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Any idea why the image doesn't show up? <\/p>\n",
